ce:section.ce:para:
To demonstrate this concept, SB-HHD-CDs were synthesized by a simple hydrothermal treatment of abundant Scutellaria barbata (SB) and Herba Hedyotis Diffusae (HHD), which are usually used to treat inflammation. Unexpectedly, SB-HHD-CDs exhibited excellent RONS scavenging ability, with rapid scavenging of superoxide anions (•O2
                     –), hydroxyl radicals (•OH), 1,1-diphenyl-2-picryl-hydrazyl radicals(DPPH) and nitric oxide radicals (•NO) at low concentrations (less than 50 μg ml−1). Due to their outstanding antioxidant activity, high thermal (20-90℃) and chemical stability under various pH conditions, the SB-HHD-CDs integrated into cigarette filter system achieved a removal capacity of more than 80% RONS during tobacco combustion at a low cost (USD 0.05 g−1) (Scheme 1
                     ). This work has successfully constructed CDs-based nanoenzymes with cost-effective and highly active RONS-scavenging abilities and provided ideas for designing carbon dots with specific functions.

Moreover, the RONS scavenging ability of SB-HHD-CDs for five cigarettes was tested continuously. The results show that the SB-HHD-CDs filter removed RONS species with exceptional scavenging efficiency. The removal efficiency for •O2
                     –, •OH, and •NO reached 82.56%, 70.22%, and 64.77%, respectively, after five cycles of sequential reuse. Finally, to evaluate the total RONS in smoke, 2′,7′-dichlorodihydrofluorescein (DCFH) was introduced. As shown in Fig. S15, as RONS reacted with DCFH in cigarette smoke without SB-HD-CDs, prominent fluorescence was observed at a peak wavelength of 525 nm. For the cigarette with SB-HHD-CDs, the fluorescence was greatly inhibited, indicating an overall RONS scavenging efficiency of 83.5%. The scavenging performance of SB-HHD-CDs on RONS generated by cigarette combustion is better than that of reported materials (Fig. 6
                     ) [40–43], and the calculated cost is much lower (USD 0.05 g−1). Despite the fact that SB-HHD-CDs are not yet capable of removing all RONS from smoke, our work suggests that they have promising potential as a new additive for fabricating improved cigarette filters and holders.
